But in truth, Boeing will probably cruise through this episode unscathed.
Analysts told The New York Times that fixing the software problem could cost Boeing $1 billion.
Another estimate for The Washington Post put the worst-case scenario at a $5.1 billion hit to Boeing over two months.
And those huge revenue streams also mean Boeing could almost certainly weather any lawsuits over the crisis.
Batteries randomly catching fire temporarily grounded the company's Dreamliner in 2013, but Boeing suffered no noticeable long-term damage as a result.